    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-ai-002",
    "text": "I don't train hard to be better than you. I train hard to be better than me yesterday.",
    "author": "Allen Iverson",
    "character": "The Answer",
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Allen_Iverson",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["growth", "self-improvement", "discipline", "competition"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-ai-003",
    "text": "Either you give in, or you fight. That's all I know, being where I'm from. You fight for what you want. You go after what you want.",
    "author": "Allen Iverson",
    "character": "The Answer",
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Allen_Iverson",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["fight", "resilience", "hustle", "origins"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "inspirational",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-mj-001",
    "text": "I've failed over and over and over again in my life. And that is why I succeed.",
    "author": "Michael Jordan",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Nike commercial",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": 1997,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["failure", "success", "persistence", "greatness"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "inspirational",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-mj-002",
    "text": "Some people want it to happen, some wish it would happen, others make it happen.",
    "author": "Michael Jordan",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["action", "ambition", "execution", "mindset"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-mj-003",
    "text": "Obstacles don't have to stop you. If you run into a wall, don't turn around and give up. Figure out how to climb it, go through it, or work around it.",
    "author": "Michael Jordan",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Michael_Jordan",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["obstacles", "resilience", "problem-solving", "persistence"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-kb-001",
    "text": "I have self-doubt. I have insecurity. I have fear of failure. We all have self-doubt. You don't deny it, but you also don't capitulate to it. You embrace it.",
    "author": "Kobe Bryant",
    "character": "Black Mamba",
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Kobe_Bryant",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["vulnerability", "fear", "courage", "self-awareness"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "philosophical",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-kb-002",
    "text": "You have to work hard in the dark to shine in the light.",
    "author": "Kobe Bryant",
    "character": "Black Mamba",
    "source": "The Mamba Mentality: How I Play",
    "sourceType": "book",
    "year": 2018,
    "isbn": "978-0374201234",
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Kobe_Bryant",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["work-ethic", "discipline", "preparation", "hustle"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "inspirational",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-kb-003",
    "text": "The mindset isn't about seeking a result — it's more about the process of getting to that result. It's about the journey and the approach. It's a way of life.",
    "author": "Kobe Bryant",
    "character": "Black Mamba",
    "source": "The Mamba Mentality: How I Play",
    "sourceType": "book",
    "year": 2018,
    "isbn": "978-0374201234",
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Kobe_Bryant",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["process", "journey", "mindset", "craft"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "philosophical",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-kb-004",
    "text": "What separates great players from all-time great players is their ability to self-assess, diagnose weaknesses, and turn those flaws into strengths.",
    "author": "Kobe Bryant",
    "character": "Black Mamba",
    "source": "The Mamba Mentality: How I Play",
    "sourceType": "book",
    "year": 2018,
    "isbn": "978-0374201234",
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Kobe_Bryant",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["self-assessment", "growth", "greatness", "iteration"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-shaq-001",
    "text": "Excellence is not a singular act, but a habit. You are what you repeatedly do.",
    "author": "Shaquille O'Neal",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Shaquille_O%27Neal",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["habits", "excellence", "discipline", "consistency"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-shaq-002",
    "text": "I'm tired of hearing about money, money, money. I just want to play the game, drink Pepsi, wear Reebok.",
    "author": "Shaquille O'Neal",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Press conference",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Shaquille_O%27Neal",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["humor", "simplicity", "play", "authenticity"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "humorous",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-jwill-001",
    "text": "I always wanted to make the extra pass, make the play nobody expected. That's what made the game beautiful to me.",
    "author": "Jason Williams",
    "character": "White Chocolate",
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": null,
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["creativity", "play", "craft", "vision"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "philosophical",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-beast-001",
    "text": "I'm just about that action, boss. I ain't ever see no talking win me nothing.",
    "author": "Marshawn Lynch",
    "character": "Beast Mode",
    "source": "Post-game press conference",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": 2014,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Marshawn_Lynch",
    "videoUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/shorts/r6xTB6xnLik",
    "tags": ["action", "authenticity", "discipline", "results"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-beast-002",
    "text": "Take care of your body, take care of your chicken, take care of your mentals.",
    "author": "Marshawn Lynch",
    "character": "Beast Mode",
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Marshawn_Lynch",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["health", "money", "mental-health", "balance"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-barry-001",
    "text": "Don't be scared to make mistakes. In life you're going to make some mistakes. Go out and play the way you're capable of.",
    "author": "Barry Sanders",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Hall of Fame enshrinement speech (quoting his father William Sanders)",
    "sourceType": "speech",
    "year": 2004,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://www.profootballhof.com/news/2005/01/news-barry-sanders-s-enshrinement-speech-transcript1/",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["mistakes", "courage", "potential", "fatherhood"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "inspirational",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-barry-002",
    "text": "Happiness does not come from football awards. Happiness comes from a good job, being able to feed your wife and kids.",
    "author": "Barry Sanders",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Barry_Sanders",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["happiness", "family", "humility", "purpose"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "philosophical",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-moss-001",
    "text": "I always played with a chip on my shoulder. It was my motivation to prove everyone wrong.",
    "author": "Randy Moss",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Randy_Moss",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["motivation", "doubt", "fuel", "proving"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "inspirational",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-moss-002",
    "text": "I love the game so much. I've been penalized. I've been fined. I have some regrets. But for those four hours on Sunday, you can be free and just let it all go.",
    "author": "Randy Moss",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Interview on retiring",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Randy_Moss",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["passion", "freedom", "regret", "play"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "philosophical",
    "maxDisplayLength": "medium",
    "addedAt": "2026-03-17",
    "addedBy": "leeview"
  },
  {
    "id": "sports-moss-003",
    "text": "Do your job. Be the best at whatever your job description is.",
    "author": "Randy Moss",
    "character": null,
    "source": "Interview",
    "sourceType": "interview",
    "year": null,
    "isbn": null,
    "url": "https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Randy_Moss",
    "videoUrl": null,
    "tags": ["craft", "focus", "excellence", "work-ethic"],
    "language": "en",
    "mood": "pragmatic",
    "maxDisplayLength": "short",
